July 18 is celebrated as Nelson Mandela International Day to honor the memory of Nelson Mandela, South Africa's first President elected by citizens of all races. Mandela fought against apartheid and prioritized human dignity and equality. The article calls for a commitment to rooting out systemic racism and promoting equity and equality. Mandela's commitment to justice, peace, and democracy allowed him to unite people across divisions. The article extends condolences to the families affected by recent violence in South Africa and emphasizes the importance of healing divisions. It concludes by honoring Mandela's vision for Africa and a brighter world.